Package: symly
Architecture: all
Depends: openjdk-17-jre-headless, libpicocli-java
Description: symly is a command-line tool for managing symbolic links.
 .
 It provides a simple and efficient way to organize and
 manage symbolic links, making it ideal for dotfile management.
 .
 With symly, you can for example centralize the dotfiles you care
 about in a single folder and manage them with Git.
